  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Beetle charges forward in a line, dealing 1 damage and pushing the first target it hits. Its 4 health is the most of any non-Alpha Vek.",
    "Strategy": "A Beetle will die if its charge goes over anyWater Tile,Lava Tile,A.C.I.D. Tile, orChasm Tile. You should encourage this behavior whenever possible, by either offering your Mechs as targets near a hazardous tile for them to charge to, or shove them so that they charge at one. Their high health can make it inefficient to dispose of them by other means.\nAlternatively, if the Beetle is first in the attack order, try to displace them so that they target another enemy; since they damageANDpush their target, look for opportunities where they can provide bump damage, push grounded enemies into water, or push another enemy away from a building. Just use caution to ensure they don't push an enemy into a building, as the bump damage will damage it even if their charge damage kills the enemy first."
  },
  "full_text": "Beetle\nDetails\nHealth\n4\nMove\n2\nSystems\nPincers\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nCharge forward to deal 1 damage and push the target.\nBeetle\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Beetle charges forward in a line, dealing 1 damage and pushing the first target it hits. Its 4 health is the most of any non-Alpha Vek.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nA Beetle will die if its charge goes over any\nWater Tile\n,\nLava Tile\n,\nA.C.I.D. Tile\n, or\nChasm Tile\n. You should encourage this behavior whenever possible, by either offering your Mechs as targets near a hazardous tile for them to charge to, or shove them so that they charge at one. Their high health can make it inefficient to dispose of them by other means.\nAlternatively, if the Beetle is first in the attack order, try to displace them so that they target another enemy; since they damage\nAND\npush their target, look for opportunities where they can provide bump damage, push grounded enemies into water, or push another enemy away from a building. Just use caution to ensure they don't push an enemy into a building, as the bump damage will damage it even if their charge damage kills the enemy first.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
